1
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:11,440
Do you have any idea how
dangerous what you did today was?

2
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:12,240
P' Le!

3
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:15,760
You could have died.

4
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:17,800
I just wanted to find the truth myself.

5
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:21,960
Because I heard your father talking to
Peem about moving some goods today.

6
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,960
Peem was never one of my father’s men.

7
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:26,800
I'm the one helping them.
You're on your own now, boss.

8
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,880
I was the one who sent Peem to my father.

9
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:31,320
Pack your things and go
back to your peaceful life.

10
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:32,880
Stop meddling in my business.

11
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,040
You know I can’t do that!

12
00:00:35,480 --> 00:00:37,320
I don't want to lose you again!

13
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,440
Can you not push me away again?

14
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:41,720
You said it yourself.

15
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:42,960
Yes.

16
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:45,160
I did.

17
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:48,600
Wait, P’ Le.

18
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,680
Our relationship now...

19
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:52,240
You’re my secretary.

20
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,480
And I’m your boss.

21
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:56,080
Is that all?

22
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:22,840
I love you, P’ Le.

23
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:26,600
I've said it.

24
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:35,640
And we did it.

25
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:02,400
I wasn't just imagining it, right, P’ Le?

26
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:08,840
There’s more to us than
just being senior and junior.

27
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:18,160
I was young back then.
I didn't understand why you pushed me away.

28
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:23,720
But now I believe you had your reasons.

29
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:29,960
Otherwise… last night would never have happened.

30
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:43,280
I’m not stupid, P’ Le.

31
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:49,160
Did you forget I was a full-scholarship student?

32
00:02:57,120 --> 00:03:03,200
If you don't die… if I don't die...
what will become of us?

33
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:06,560
Would we be lovers?

34
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:08,960
A family?

35
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,480
Would we get to build a house?

36
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:16,160
Go on road trips like I’ve dreamed of?

37
00:03:30,079 --> 00:03:31,480
Or if I have to die,

38
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:36,600
I’ll do everything I can to make sure
I don't have the same regrets as last time.

39
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,320
Have some breakfast first, P’ Le.

40
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,600
We actually have time today?

41
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,400
Usually you're just rushing me to work.

42
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:18,920
'Time's up,' 'Coffee break's over,'

43
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:23,120
'Meeting in the morning, meeting in
the afternoon, meeting in the evening...'

44
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:27,600
I’m not sure which one of
us is the workaholic anymore.

45
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,360
We've got some time today.

46
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,600
Aren't you going to ask me 'time for what'?

47
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,480
So you're calling me intimately now?

48
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,200
You gave me permission, didn't you?

49
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,720
P’… Le.

50
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:21,920
Do I… really need to ask?

51
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,320
So what is this time for?

52
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,159
Time to win your heart.

53
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,800
You were the one who said we don't have a status.

54
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:50,720
If that's the case... then I'd like
to use this time to win your heart.

55
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:10,120
I’m actually embarrassed for her, P’ Dia.

56
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,720
Embarrassed for what?

57
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,800
I mean, look at her! Look at our boss.

58
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:19,200
She’s acting all aloof, but her
fingers are twitching like crazy.

59
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:24,280
She’s dying to pull Rann in for a hug,
but she has to act ‘classy’ and ‘composed.’

60
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,160
Her pride is practically choking her.

61
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:27,680
Watching her makes my neck hurt.

62
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:33,840
All we can do is hope she finally
listens to what her heart is telling her.

63
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:38,320
You mean the part that's screaming,
'Code Red! Code Red! Heart under invasion!'?

64
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,520
Aren't you leaving?

65
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:14,960
I’m tidying up.

66
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,960
In case you need anything else from me.

67
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:23,880
I don't.

68
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:41,960
Wait.

69
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:44,760
Do you like me now?

70
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:47,560
No.

71
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,120
Go get Peem for me.

72
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:52,200
Is that all?

73
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,840
Of course. What else would there be?

74
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,160
Thought you were gonna say something else.

75
00:09:58,280 --> 00:10:02,200
I feel like my 'star secretary'
is being unprofessional today.

76
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,720
I'll go get him right away.

77
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:12,120
You usually call him yourself just fine.

78
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,200
Go on.

79
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,680
Let them know that these are the final figures.

80
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,400
Oops!

81
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:52,840
Sorry.

82
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,440
If I hadn't caught you, you’d
have hit the floor head-first.

83
00:10:59,080 --> 00:10:59,920
Thank you.

84
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:03,960
Make it more believable next time.

85
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:09,600
This girl…

86
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:19,520
Here is the information you requested, Khun Lené.

87
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,400
Oh, and regarding the shipments from Europe.

88
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:27,120
They haven't been imported yet because
there are some concerns about the import taxes.

89
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:28,480
Which shipment is this?

90
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,400
Uh…

91
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,440
The details are all here, Khun Lené.

92
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:38,040
What is it?

93
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:41,520
We're just happy.

94
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:45,720
It’s nice to finally see you have
a secretary who knows you well.

95
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:52,720
That's right. Usually, anyone who
works for you doesn't even last a month.

96
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:59,240
Are you suggesting that I lack patience?

97
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,400
No! That’s not what we’re thinking at all!

98
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,280
Really! I swear!

99
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,440
Oh! Three fingers.

100
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:09,120
I'm sure they didn't mean it like that.

101
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:10,960
- Exactly, Nong Rann!
- Right!

102
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:14,000
But they probably mean that
I’m the perfect match for you, P’ Le.

103
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,080
I mean, Khun Lené.

104
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,640
…As your secretary.

105
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:27,240
Aran, get me some coffee.

106
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:31,680
I thought you’d have me instead.

107
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,520
Gosh! That was so bold!

108
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:45,000
Are you smiling, Khun Lené?

109
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,600
Ouch! What?

110
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,880
Why have you stopped? Keep going.

111
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:54,320
Oh! Yes! W-w-we're working!

112
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:56,240
We're doing it.

113
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:58,360
Working, working. We’re working.

114
00:12:58,920 --> 00:12:59,840
Which page are we on?

115
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:10,680
Who is it?

116
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,160
It’s me, Rann.

117
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:13,800
Come in.

118
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,320
Are you trying to burn a hole through me?

119
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,720
If this is a bad time, maybe I should leave.

120
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,200
When did I say it was a bad time?

121
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:45,640
B-but... you’re teasing me.

122
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,320
So what do you want? I'm listening.

123
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:57,320
I'm going to see Khun Kanin tomorrow.

124
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,640
What for?

125
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:05,680
We need to find out if he's suspicious of me yet.

126
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:11,480
I think the reason he's
paying me such a high salary

127
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,960
is because he wants me to
feed him information about you.

128
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:21,720
If he still thinks I'm on his side,
I might be able to dig up more evidence.

129
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,160
It’s too dangerous.

130
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:27,960
We don’t even know if he’s realized
it was you at the warehouse that night.

131
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:31,000
That’s exactly why I have to go.

132
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:33,280
No. I won’t allow it.

133
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:35,440
I wasn't asking for permission.

134
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:47,400
P’Le, I don’t want you to find out
later and end up doubting me.

135
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,680
That’s why I’m giving you a heads-up.

136
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:52,840
But you can’t stop me, P’Le.

137
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:08,840
Don’t push yourself too far.

138
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:15,040
Then I'll head to bed now.

139
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,760
Goodnight.

140
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,000
Wait.

141
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:31,000
For the past few days… you’ve
been making a move on me, right?

142
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:36,880
Stopping already?

143
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:43,000
Are you getting back at me
for being stubborn, P’Le?

144
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,240
So you're aware...

145
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:53,160
that you're... stubborn.

146
00:15:56,920 --> 00:16:03,880
And are you aware... that
you're being just as irrational?

147
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:33,000
Then do you want this irrational girl...
to flirt with you for a change?

148
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,280
…Noo Rann.

149
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,800
Stop flirting and come dry my hair.

150
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,240
You did that on purpose.

151
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,160
You’re the worst.

152
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:26,760
I heard that.

153
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,920
Is that how you want to play it?

154
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:47,840
Hey, P’Le! Don't tease me like this.

155
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,200
How am I teasing you?

156
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:51,040
Getting me turned on but doing nothing.

157
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:10,720
I already did, didn't I?
Was that night not enough for you?

158
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:33,320
Since when did you become like this?

159
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,880
I’ve always been this way.

160
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:42,680
But a certain someone…
just kept pushing me away.

161
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:51,200
I’m glad you’re still the same.

162
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:59,080
Time for bed. I’m sleepy.

163
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:27,720
There he is.

164
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,440
The future of our company.

165
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,560
You’re speaking the truth, Uncle.

166
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:36,400
Have a seat.

167
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:38,400
Can I get you a drink?

168
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:39,440
I'm good.

169
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:44,080
Let’s get down to business.
I have an appointment later.

170
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,000
It’s a date, Uncle.

171
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:52,040
You’re not interested in my daughter anymore?

172
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,600
You know, Lené is quite a beauty.

173
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:59,360
She’s beautiful, I’ll give you that.

174
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,480
But she has zero interest in me.

175
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:08,080
Besides... being too capable can be a problem.

176
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:13,000
Otherwise, why else would you have chosen me

177
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:16,280
to help you oust her from the board?

178
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,040
Am I right?

179
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,560
Don’t exaggerate.

180
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:27,960
I just want my daughter to live an easy life.

181
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:34,400
Wear beautiful clothes, have
time to find a lover, go on trips.

182
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,720
Be happy like other young women.

183
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,320
But she won’t go along with it, will she?

184
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,600
Stubborn just like her mother.

185
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:49,200
And because she’s like this,
everyone else is dissatisfied.

186
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,000
Now, they’re putting the pressure on me.

187
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:57,400
Which is exactly why
I have to turn to you for help.

188
00:20:58,160 --> 00:20:59,400
I understand you, Uncle.

189
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:03,800
Children should be obedient
like they’re expected to be.

190
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:09,600
I knew you'd understand me.

191
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:15,920
And the matter with the shares...
how is that coming along?

192
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,480
Don't you worry about that, Uncle.

193
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:21,760
I’m having my people handle
this as quietly as possible.

194
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:27,480
By the time Khun Lené realizes it...
it’ll be too late to do anything.

195
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:45,680
Come in.

196
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:59,920
Is something the matter?
You suddenly said you wanted to see me.

197
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,840
Um... well...

198
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:10,280
You said to let you know right
away if Khun Lené acted strangely.

199
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:22,160
Well... it’s just that, last Friday night...
something strange happened.

200
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:29,560
But I'm not sure if it's exactly
what you told me to look out for.

201
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:38,120
It's okay.
Just calm down and take your time.

202
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,920
Khun Lené was gone the entire night.

203
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:50,600
And the next morning, I saw
her clothes… stained with blood.

204
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:58,920
What did you say, P’ Le?

205
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:04,720
I said, go ahead and tell my father
that I came back injured that night.

206
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:06,520
But…

207
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:08,920
Either way, he already knows it was me.

208
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:12,680
Not many people dare to go after him.

209
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:16,040
He just hasn't found any concrete evidence yet.

210
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:21,520
Sooner or later, I'm going to
have to clash with my father.

211
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:24,960
If you want to earn his trust,

212
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:30,360
just confirm his suspicion
that it was my doing that night.

213
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,640
You insist on going anyway, right?

214
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:57,600
When I saw that Khun Lené hadn't
come back, I waited up until morning.

215
00:23:58,240 --> 00:24:01,480
But when she finally made it home,

216
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:06,320
Khun Lené hurried up to
her room and called P’ Dia in.

217
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:10,120
Then I saw in the laundry room

218
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:14,480
that the clothes Khun Lené wore
were stained with blood.

219
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:19,920
How are you so sure it was blood?

220
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:25,920
The... the smell. It was metallic.

221
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:31,360
Did I do something wrong?

222
00:24:32,320 --> 00:24:35,200
Or should I have just ignored it?

223
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,360
No, you did the right thing.

224
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,080
Is there anything else?

225
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:47,640
No.

226
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:55,800
Thank you. You may return to your work now.

227
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:58,360
Yes.

228
00:25:09,520 --> 00:25:10,360
Hold on.

229
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:21,720
Were you at Lené's place
the entire night that night?

230
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:27,360
Yes. I was on the phone with a friend all night.

231
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:29,240
Do you want to check, Khun Kanin?

232
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:35,000
No, I was just asking.

233
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:37,320
You can go back to work.

234
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:41,920
Oh.

235
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,600
And thanks so much for telling me.

236
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:52,080
Just keep a close eye on Lené from now on.

237
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,200
What just happened in there?

238
00:26:27,160 --> 00:26:28,640
Did my father do something to you?

239
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:40,760
Your father…

240
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,920
his eyes were so scary
as if he could see through me.

241
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:49,520
I thought I was going to get caught.

242
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:57,760
That's why I told you not to do it.

243
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:01,560
But I pulled it off.

244
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:04,560
Your father seemed to believe me.

245
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:06,000
You call this pulling it off?

246
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:10,200
Standing here looking pale and shaking?

247
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:14,440
I just can’t believe you.

248
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,400
Why are you smiling?

249
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:32,760
I'm just happy you're worried about me.

250
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:37,840
I— I'm worried about you?

251
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,120
What makes you think I'm worried?

252
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:54,520
P' Le! Someone might see us.

253
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,600
Not smiling anymore?

254
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:27,720
P' Le! When did you become so bad?

255
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,400
Forgive me, P’ Le.

256
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:45,320
It was so hard to get my hands
on your father’s schedule.

257
00:28:45,520 --> 00:28:50,200
If I told you what I was going to do,
you’d just try to stop me again.

258
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:52,960
Sure.

259
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:06,120
Whatever you're looking for, make it quick.

260
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:10,200
The president doesn't like people messing
around in his office while he's out.

261
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:12,240
Yes, thank you so much.

262
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:15,320
Those earrings were a keepsake
from my grandmother.

263
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:16,640
They really mean the world to me.

264
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:18,560
Go ahead.

265
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:20,440
Thank you.

266
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:30,400
Oh my god, I spilled coffee!

267
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:32,040
- What do I do? Oh my god!
- What now?

268
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:33,960
Find it quickly and get out.

269
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:34,760
Okay.

270
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:37,400
What's all the racket out there?!

271
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,440
Oh my god, where's the janitor?!
Do we have a rag?

272
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:51,160
What's with the commotion?!

273
00:29:51,320 --> 00:29:53,880
Oh, Miss. I'm so sorry.

274
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:57,280
I just came up from buying
coffee for the department.

275
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:59,840
I didn't mean to trip and
make such a huge mess.

276
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:00,920
I'm really sorry!

277
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:09,800
What do I do?

278
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:13,200
Wait, Miss! Hold on.
Um, where should I start cleaning first?

279
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:16,040
Wipe it up wherever you spilled it!

280
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:18,800
Wait, Miss! Can I use this document?

281
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:21,520
- Can I take this?
- That's an important document! You can’t use it!

282
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:37,520
- Ugh!
- Okay.

283
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:40,680
Oh, Miss! Wait!
Can I use your jacket to wipe it?

284
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:42,480
Are you crazy?! Use yours!

285
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:50,280
Okay. Oh god, I’m sorry.
Gotta find a rag.

286
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:51,760
Oh, right! I'll come with you.

287
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:52,680
- Let's go.
- For god's sake!

288
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:54,160
You’re such a nuisance!

289
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:57,440
You still haven't found it?

290
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,000
Found it!

291
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:12,200
Thank you.

292
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:19,320
Just cause a scene outside, right, P' Rann?

293
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:20,200
Yeah.

294
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:23,400
- And also…
- Don't worry, my lips are sealed.

295
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,360
Thank you.

296
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:30,360
And what are you standing here for?
Clean up the mess! All of it!

297
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:32,400
Can't borrow your jacket, I guess?

298
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:36,000
Sorry. I'll even clean the windows. Bye!

299
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,760
How is it? Did you get anything?

300
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:53,840
Let me remind you, I'm a graphic
designer who only knows a bit of IT.

301
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:56,760
Says the person who hacked major companies.

302
00:31:56,800 --> 00:32:00,360
Okay, fine, but I only changed their
banners to something funny back then.

303
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:01,680
I don't do that anymore.

304
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:04,480
Not only am I risking prison,
but now I'm gonna miss my deadline too.

305
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:09,520
Please help me out.
Just this once, I promise.

306
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:13,480
Fine, alright.
But you'll have to wait a bit.

307
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:18,080
We need the owner to turn on the computer
first before I can extract any data.

308
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:20,880
But keep in mind, it's only a 'maybe.’

309
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:22,880
Thanks, Gen.

310
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:26,360
Yeah. We've only got each other anyway.

311
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:32,560
But once this is all over, you
better tell me absolutely everything.

312
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:34,200
Yeah.

313
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:37,200
Once this is all over.

314
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:38,520
Mhm.

315
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:51,360
It's okay.

316
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,320
You can do this.

317
00:32:54,120 --> 00:32:55,600
You can do it for P’ Le.

318
00:32:57,080 --> 00:32:59,080
I won't screw up like at the warehouse.

319
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:10,480
Uh, insurance.
An insurance agent called.

320
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:15,040
I didn't say anything.

321
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:30,640
Wow.

322
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:33,760
Momma, this place is amazing!
Where on earth did you find it?

323
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:35,880
Come on, where else do you think?

324
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:39,320
She’s on TikTok all day, glued to her phone!

325
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:41,600
Oh please! Like you aren't glued to yours?

326
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:44,960
I saw it—'onsens near me,' secret
chats, private groups, male models...

327
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:47,880
Your IG is just filled with guys in underwear.

328
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:49,120
It's only the good stuff.

329
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:50,520
Right?

330
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:53,960
Is it really that good? Let me see.

331
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:56,560
I'm afraid it might make you scream.

332
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:58,960
I never scream.

333
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:00,560
Ugh, P’ Fiu!

334
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:02,440
What?

335
00:34:03,640 --> 00:34:04,640
Just ignore them.

336
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:07,120
How are you holding up?
Settling in alright?

337
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,600
Pretty well, yeah.

338
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:13,639
P’ Rann can definitely handle it.
Right, P’ Rann?

339
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:21,080
Uh, P’ Rann.

340
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:25,800
Actually, the girls just want to
know about you and our boss.

341
00:34:26,159 --> 00:34:27,360
You little snitch!

342
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:38,000
Not to be nosy, Rann, but do you and
Khun Lené have some kind of history?

343
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,840
At first, she looked like she hated your guts.

344
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:43,639
Normally, if you make one tiny
mistake, she’ll rip you to shreds.

345
00:34:43,679 --> 00:34:46,360
During meetings, I’d shake so hard
you'd think I was possessed.

346
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:48,040
But lately, she’s softened up a lot.

347
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:50,520
Yesterday, she just said, "Go fix this."
That was it!

348
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:52,600
Totally! I couldn't agree with you more.

349
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,239
Khun Lené isn't really that fierce.

350
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:59,360
Girl! In what world is she not fierce?!

351
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:02,600
Wait... do you know something we don't?

352
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:05,920
- Aha!
- I knew it. Spill it. Now.

353
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:08,800
I wanna know too.
What's the deal? What do you know?

354
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:16,560
I have a call coming in.
Please excuse me for a moment.

355
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:18,640
Go ahead.

356
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:30,280
Hello?

357
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:31,880
Where are you, Khun Rann?

358
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,920
I'm out having lunch with the team.

359
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,560
Does Khun Lené need something?

360
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:41,720
Geez, the second you open your mouth,
you're already asking about Khun Lené.

361
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:45,200
If that's all, I'm going to hang up now.

362
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:47,880
Wait.
Which restaurant are you eating at?

363
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:50,960
- Sorry?
- A certain someone is curious.

364
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:52,040
Ouch!

365
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:54,720
So, which restaurant is it?

366
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:57,560
It's the cafe across from the office alley.

367
00:35:58,480 --> 00:36:00,200
Take the first turn in and you'll see it.

368
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:03,080
Got it. Stay right there.
Someone is coming to pick you up.

369
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:06,520
Oh, and you don't need to
come back to the office today.

370
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,520
You can just go home and rest.

371
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:16,320
It's been a while…

372
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:19,440
Khun Rann.

373
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,280
Khun Dean.

374
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:31,120
You’re hitting harder every day, Khun Lené.

375
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:36,000
You're starting to feel like one of
your father's smuggled weapons.

376
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:41,000
One of these days, you're gonna
blast a hole right through my arm.

377
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:45,240
If you don't watch your mouth,
your whole body will be riddled with holes.

378
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:51,120
As long as I don't die...
I don't mind a couple of extra holes.

379
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:02,560
Peem.

380
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:06,320
What am I supposed to do?

381
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:10,760
You've already gone so soft on her.
Why are you even asking me?

382
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:16,560
But you know exactly why I sent her abroad.

383
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:23,280
Then you should know better
than anyone why she came back.

384
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:29,400
Things have already gone
past the point of no return.

385
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:33,560
Maybe the safest place for her...

386
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:36,800
is right by your side.

387
00:37:40,520 --> 00:37:41,760
Besides!

388
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:47,120
You don't actually have the heart
to send her back anyway, do you?

389
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:48,440
Know-it-all!

390
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:52,160
Would you look at that smile?

391
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,160
Oop! Heh, missed me!

392
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:57,560
Better get moving. Let's go.

393
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:03,760
It's been a while since that
last board meeting, hasn’t it?

394
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:06,600
Right.

395
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:11,160
But I have a feeling we'll be seeing
a lot more of each other from now on.

396
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:13,520
After all, I still have to drop by the office.

397
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:15,960
How about this?

398
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:20,640
I’ll ask Khun Lené to
assign you to look after me.

399
00:38:21,520 --> 00:38:25,600
Since I still don't know
much about this organization.

400
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:28,160
If you're by my side...

401
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:32,080
I’m sure you could show me the ropes.

402
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,920
I don't think I'm that capable.

403
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:40,040
But I think you are.

404
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:43,600
Just one look at you...

405
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:47,120
and I can tell.

406
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:53,920
Why?

407
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:59,600
Don’t you… want to be with me?

408
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:04,080
I have just as much to offer
as Khun Le, you know.

409
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:15,840
I'm not sure if I'm mistaken, but
I doubt you'll have the time to drop by.

410
00:39:16,400 --> 00:39:21,040
Because you have other
companies to run besides this one.

411
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:29,040
I'm glad you're interested enough
in me to check my background.

412
00:39:30,920 --> 00:39:32,320
Everybody knows that.

413
00:39:33,160 --> 00:39:35,400
There was no need for me to look you up.

414
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:38,000
Am I being rejected?

415
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:46,560
But I'm interested in you.

416
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:50,720
Please let me go.

417
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:56,480
Don’t you want to know about Khun Le?

418
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:11,280
Should I go get her instead?

419
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:16,200
Stay put if you still want a job.

420
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:41,920
P’ Le!

421
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:44,360
Don't cross the line.

422
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:50,760
Come with me.

423
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:53,480
P’ Le, let me explain.

424
00:41:00,080 --> 00:41:01,080
What's going on, boss?

425
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:02,720
Out of the way!

426
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:07,480
Wait—

427
00:41:09,520 --> 00:41:10,360
What the hell?

428
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:16,480
What were you doing with him?!

429
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:17,520
Doing what?

430
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:20,840
I didn't do anything!
What's gotten into you, P’ Le?

431
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:22,800
You have the nerve to ask me that?!

432
00:41:23,240 --> 00:41:24,680
What do you think I saw back there?

433
00:41:25,120 --> 00:41:26,800
Do you think I’m blind?!

434
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:29,920
And you have the nerve
to say you're pursuing me?!

435
00:41:30,040 --> 00:41:31,320
That you're coming back to me?!

436
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:33,640
That you want to be more than this?

437
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:37,320
While you're out kissing him in broad daylight?!

438
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:40,200
How shameless of you to ask me what's wrong!

439
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:45,320
It's not what you think, P’ Le.
I didn't do anything!

440
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:49,040
Do you take me for a fool
who'll just believe anything you say?!

441
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:54,400
Did you think I didn't know you've
been secretly talking to someone?

442
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,800
Lying constantly just to hide it from me?

443
00:41:59,120 --> 00:42:02,920
Uh, insurance.
An insurance agent called.

444
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:05,640
No.

445
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:07,760
It's not what you think.

446
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:09,200
Then what is it?!

447
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:13,760
Oh, I forgot. You lived abroad for so long.

448
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:18,200
Maybe kissing a couple
of guys is no big deal to you.

449
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:20,200
But it sure as hell is to me!

450
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:24,120
I don't like sluts who
throw themselves at everyone.

451
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:26,280
- P’ Le!
- Don't call me that!

452
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:28,560
I'm not your P’ Le.

453
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:35,640
Fine… Khun Lené.

454
00:42:38,080 --> 00:42:39,920
Since you say we're nothing to each other,

455
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:43,480
then who I kiss, who I hug,

456
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:47,040
or who I screw is none of your business!

457
00:42:48,520 --> 00:42:50,280
What right do you have to be jealous?

458
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:52,320
What right do you have to call me a slut?!

459
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:58,960
You have no right to me, just as
I have no right to call you ‘P’ Le’!

460
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:03,880
You want that damn right so badly?!

461
00:43:04,320 --> 00:43:05,040
Fine!

462
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:07,280
Then let's set a status.

463
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:10,560
Hookup partners. How about that?!

464
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:14,400
If not, then get the hell out of my life!

465
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:17,480
Get out!

466
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:27,680
~ I can only look back on days
that have turned to dust ~

467
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:35,800
~ A Time when I let you walk away ~

468
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:38,560
~ I was blind to the truth ~

469
00:43:38,600 --> 00:43:40,720
~ Thinking it was for the best ~

470
00:43:41,760 --> 00:43:44,520
~ Only then did I find out about you ~

471
00:43:45,080 --> 00:43:47,800
~ Only then did I realize that you were gone ~

472
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:53,280
~ As if the heavens saw my sorrow ~

473
00:43:53,320 --> 00:43:57,920
~ They guided us back to each other ~

474
00:43:57,960 --> 00:44:01,320
~ After the day we were suddenly torn apart ~

475
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:06,480
~ They let me return to your side ~

476
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:09,760
~ To know how much you mean to me ~

477
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:13,320
~ And just how much I love you ~

478
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:24,520
~ Since the moment of my return ~

479
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:27,760
~ I realized I came back for you ~

480
00:44:27,760 --> 00:44:30,520
~ I’ve come back to make things right ~

481
00:44:30,560 --> 00:44:34,440
~ For the day I left you all alone ~
I'm sorry.

482
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:41,280
~ From now on, I’ll never let you slip away ~

483
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:44,160
~ With every breath I take ~

484
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:49,760
Rann, I’m sorry.
~ I’ll make up to you for the time we lost ~

485
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:15,760
Rann, wait.

486
00:45:19,520 --> 00:45:20,760
Can we please talk?

487
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:23,880
I was wrong.

488
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:28,720
If you're ready, Khun Lené,
then let's get straight to work.

489
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:25,840
Rann, can we please talk?

490
00:46:27,160 --> 00:46:29,120
I don't know what got into me that day.

491
00:46:34,520 --> 00:46:36,480
Do you need anything, Khun Lené?

492
00:46:38,800 --> 00:46:39,720
Rann…

493
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:45,680
This is a workplace.

494
00:46:46,160 --> 00:46:48,360
I wouldn't want you accusing
me of being irresponsible.

495
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:51,960
Or using something other than
my brain to get the job done.

496
00:46:54,840 --> 00:46:55,920
- I didn't mean to—
- P’ Rann.

497
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:00,360
What is it, Itim?

498
00:47:00,360 --> 00:47:02,840
P' Punch asked me to bring
this over for you to look at.

499
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:06,040
Let me take a look.

500
00:47:09,680 --> 00:47:10,720
Where do I sign?

501
00:47:10,760 --> 00:47:12,400
Here, here, and here.

502
00:47:47,920 --> 00:47:50,840
Hello? Send me your latest collection.

503
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:55,280
This is all I could get.

504
00:48:04,560 --> 00:48:07,000
TOP SECRET

505
00:48:08,360 --> 00:48:09,640
All that trouble to get this...

506
00:48:10,960 --> 00:48:12,680
But I guess she doesn't want it anymore.

507
00:48:29,520 --> 00:48:30,480
Rann, hold on.

508
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:35,960
Yes, Khun Lené.

509
00:48:46,080 --> 00:48:46,920
What is this?

510
00:48:47,360 --> 00:48:48,240
Take it.

511
00:49:13,920 --> 00:49:15,960
I noticed you always wear the same necklace.

512
00:49:17,360 --> 00:49:18,240
Do you like it?

513
00:49:23,120 --> 00:49:24,280
Why are you giving me this?

514
00:49:24,920 --> 00:49:27,640
Because... I wanted to.

515
00:49:34,160 --> 00:49:37,200
So I'm supposed to say,
'Thank you so much, Boss,

516
00:49:37,200 --> 00:49:42,320
for buying your secretary a necklace
after calling her an easy woman'?

517
00:49:46,360 --> 00:49:48,000
Take your necklace back.

518
00:49:52,080 --> 00:49:53,720
What if it's my way of apologizing?

519
00:49:58,400 --> 00:49:59,440
All this time…

520
00:50:02,240 --> 00:50:04,160
is that who you thought I was?

521
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:12,360
I already have my own,

522
00:50:12,880 --> 00:50:17,360
and it's worth thousands of times
more than what you're giving me.

523
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:21,120
Can we make up?

524
00:50:25,800 --> 00:50:27,320
What is there for us to make up about?

525
00:50:28,440 --> 00:50:32,600
How do I make it up to you?
How do I apologize for you to forgive me?

526
00:50:34,880 --> 00:50:36,360
And why do you even need to?

527
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:41,000
You're the boss, and I'm the secretary.

528
00:50:42,160 --> 00:50:43,120
That's all.

529
00:50:43,560 --> 00:50:45,240
Rann, it's not like that.

530
00:50:45,520 --> 00:50:48,520
Oh, or did you just see me as a hookup partner?

531
00:50:48,920 --> 00:50:50,440
If so, this is even less necessary.

532
00:50:51,960 --> 00:50:55,920
Does a mere hookup partner even
have the right to demand anything?

533
00:50:58,160 --> 00:51:00,720
It's my fault.
I should never have said that.

534
00:51:04,720 --> 00:51:06,400
Excuse me, we have to go.

535
00:51:07,520 --> 00:51:09,120
Someone’s giving you a ride, Khun Rann.

536
00:51:11,880 --> 00:51:13,840
Another secret I'm not supposed to know?

537
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:19,360
Is the driver waiting downstairs?

538
00:51:21,880 --> 00:51:24,440
Then I should head down now.
Don't want to keep them waiting.

539
00:51:41,280 --> 00:51:42,000
Just go.

540
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:03,200
Hi, darling!

541
00:52:04,560 --> 00:52:06,560
Watch it, or she'll smash
your head with a bottle.

542
00:52:08,480 --> 00:52:09,560
How about 'babe' then?

543
00:52:11,240 --> 00:52:13,520
Or 'honey'? Hmm?

544
00:52:20,080 --> 00:52:22,080
- What's wrong with her?
- Trouble with the missus.

545
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:34,400
Want a drink?
Something cold might cool you down.

546
00:52:35,960 --> 00:52:37,120
Can we just get to the point?

547
00:52:38,440 --> 00:52:41,200
Come on, stop being mad.

548
00:52:42,040 --> 00:52:45,680
Didn't I tell you it was all a misunderstanding?

549
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:51,600
Look, I’ve never even
given your girl a single kiss.

550
00:52:52,280 --> 00:52:56,720
All I asked was, 'Have you ever seen
a picture of Miss Lené when she was five?’

551
00:52:57,280 --> 00:53:00,480
Back then, you cried because I took your doll.

552
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:02,120
You even whacked me non-stop.

553
00:53:03,400 --> 00:53:09,080
I had to pat your head and
say, 'There, there, it's okay.'

554
00:53:09,480 --> 00:53:10,400
That's all!

555
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:17,920
But your girl was smiling so sweetly,
like she was in Candy World.

556
00:53:18,400 --> 00:53:20,960
But the moment you showed up... boom!

557
00:53:22,480 --> 00:53:23,520
I know.

558
00:53:23,880 --> 00:53:24,760
You do?!

559
00:53:26,800 --> 00:53:27,920
That’s it?

560
00:53:30,560 --> 00:53:32,160
You’re not nice at all.

561
00:53:33,320 --> 00:53:36,000
I'm literally your only childhood friend.

562
00:53:38,960 --> 00:53:40,000
How hurtful.

563
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:46,840
You asked for help, and I came right away.

564
00:53:48,520 --> 00:53:50,200
You were way more adorable as a kid.

565
00:53:59,160 --> 00:53:59,960
What's that?

566
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:11,520
Okay.

567
00:54:12,840 --> 00:54:13,760
Let’s do this.

568
00:54:14,760 --> 00:54:17,240
Hmm... where should we start?

569
00:54:21,480 --> 00:54:26,360
Should we start with your dad
trying to kick you out of the board?

570
00:54:27,440 --> 00:54:31,920
Or... how about your plan to backstab him?

571
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:39,240
"P’ Le was wrong. Completely wrong.
Can you forgive this foolish girl? Please?”

572
00:55:44,520 --> 00:55:47,360
Oh, so now you're 'P' this and ‘P’ that?

573
00:55:48,960 --> 00:55:51,160
How did she grow up to be such a brat?

574
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:18,960
Rann, can we please talk?

575
00:56:24,160 --> 00:56:27,120
Guess what goes around comes around, huh?

576
00:56:27,400 --> 00:56:29,880
I’m sorry. I was jealous.

577
00:56:30,280 --> 00:56:33,600
I thought you were on your period.
You went totally ballistic.

578
00:56:34,880 --> 00:56:38,240
Can we make a quick stop before going home?

579
00:56:38,880 --> 00:56:41,160
Thank you for coming back.

580
00:56:45,160 --> 00:56:46,120
This isn’t real.

581
00:56:51,960 --> 00:56:54,960
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.
